    <prj:ScienceGoal>
        <prj:name>Imaging the host galaxy's cool ISM,  97-GHz radio emission and molecular outflows</prj:name>
        <prj:note>The target is a very powerful AGN hidden behind 0.5 mag of galactic extinction. We are proposing observations to reveal its internal structure and dynamics after PSF-subtracting the nuclear emission, and have two-band JVLA observations approved under grade-B. 

With ALMA we propose to determine the distribution of continuum and molecular gas emission throughout the multiple components, revealing internal motion, tracing the relative motion of the bulk of the molecular gas. Alongside, we will detect the cool continuum, and any synchrotron emission in comparison with higher resolution observations. 
The integrated flux in the CO(1-0) line is known to be 1.45Jy km/s 
(Yun et al. 2004), and we have compiled a thorough far-IR-submm SED using Herschel and SCUBA2, allowing an accurate extrapolation to 97.3GHz. </prj:note>
