    <prj:ScienceGoal>
        <prj:name>Imaging warm molecular gas</prj:name>
        <prj:note>We propose to obtain observations of CO(3-2) at a matched spatial and 
spectral resolution to CO(1-0) in order to compare the line ratios and 
velocity profile of emission from the host galaxy, the precincts of 
the AGN and any high-velocity outflow. We expect CO(1-0) and CO(3-2) lines 
to be excited in all regions of the target. We know the expected 
continuum flux density of the galaxy, and so we can also make a 
detailed dust distribution map, and be sure that there is no missing flux. 
We also augment this search with observations in Band-9 to probe even more 
excited material using both lines and continuum.  </prj:note>
