    <prj:ScienceGoal>
        <prj:name>Line and continuum imaging nearer to the SED peak</prj:name>
        <prj:note>We propose to observe at the frequencies of CO(7-6) and CI in the target to obtain the best possible spatial resolution, to better separate the emission from the AGN and the host galaxy, in the dust continuum, and to probe the higher-excitation gas likely to found in any active star-forming regions of the host, and near to the AGN. High-velocity molecular gas, flowing out from the vicinity of the AGN should also be detectable most easily in this transtion. 

The relative sensitivity of observations for this target means that continuum detection is assured, and line detection should be possible. 
The excellent spatial resolution from the warm dust will provide a very powerful constraint on the relative strength of host and AGN emission. </prj:note>
